Impact
IDORs range from low to critical depending on what object is exposed:

Low — reading non-sensitive public-ish data
Medium — reading another user's private data (messages, orders, PII)
High — modifying or deleting another user's data
Critical — account takeover, accessing admin functionality, bulk data exposure

Bug bounty programs pay well for IDORs — especially ones that expose PII or allow unauthorized writes.

